<font color="#FF0000">THE WALL</font><br>
<tt>Wed Jan  8 23:08:32 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
I visit the Wall at least three times a year. The day I left my unit to return to the US, I was notified of the death of a friend made during infantry training. Whatever else I may do in DC, I make sure that I stop at 29W, and say a prayer for Skip and his family. The Memorial has a simple dignity about it that I find more eloquent than many flashier monuments.
<p><code>-- turtle@plantaganet.com  (Gerald Alan Ney) </code><p>


